msgid "<a name=\"navpanels\">\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#, no-wrap
msgid "Navigating The Panels of the Message Tab (Tab, Escape)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"This hereby concerns the tab containing the following panels: folder tree "
"view, message list, header pane and message preview (shown or hidden via the "
"F8 key)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"TAB: Moves to the next panel. This shortcut will be more ergonomic for some "
"people than F6;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid "Escape: Returns to the previous panel. Equivalent to Shift+F6;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "Note:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"When tabbing from the message list to reach the text, the header area is "
"skipped. To reach this header area, press Alt+one digit on the alphanumeric "
"keyboard three times quickly, then press Escape to exit the header context "
"menu. These Alt+digit shortcuts reduce the need to go to the header "
"area. For more details, see the \"Header viewing\" section below.  \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "<a name=\"threadTree\">\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#, no-wrap
msgid "Message List, Preview Pane And Separate Reading Window "
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Some of the following shortcuts are common to these three contexts, others "
"relate to a particular context."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "<a name=\"attach\">\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#, no-wrap
msgid "Accessing Attachments (Alt+Page down) "
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Alt+page down or Alt+p: if the preview pane is displayed (via F8), Opens the "
"list of attachments for the selected message;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Alt+9 or number 1 or 2: only from the message list, one press states the "
"number of attachments, two presses open the list of attachments;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "<a name=\"readPreview\">\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#, no-wrap
msgid "Quick And Uncluttered Message Reading "
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Quick message reading commands are available in three contexts: from the "
"message list, from a message opened in a tab or from a message opened in a "
"separate window;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid "They are now all compatible with messages from Framalistes;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Most quick-reading keyboard shortcuts have been concentrated to minimize "
"hand movement during a session of reading many messages;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"A single press of the main key of a shortcut starts the uncluttered reading "
"of the message, i.e. with strongly shortened quote headers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"A double press starts reading the message in its original form. The terms "
"\"unfiltered reading\" are synonymous;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "<a name=\"readFromList\">\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ####
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Quick Message Reading From The List Without Leaving It (Spacebar, F4 or "
"Alt+down arrow) "
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"To benefit from this feature, you will have to display the message reading "
"pane with the F8 key first. By pressing this key, you will hear if this pane "
"is present or absent;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "Next, go to the message list and use the following keys:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Space, Alt+Down Arrow or F4: Reads the message body without leaving the "
"list. After reading a message, press down arrow then Space or Alt+down arrow "
"or F4 to hear the next message;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Double-keystroke, displays the list of links in a message if Chichi is "
"active. If an RSS feed article is selected, it will be opened in the "
"Internet browser;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Shift+space, Alt+Up arrow or Shift+f4: same function in addition to reading "
"quotes in their chronological order (from bottom to top);"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"And to complete the commands available from the message list, let's mention "
"here:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Letter n or Alt+Right arrow: selects the next unread message, even across "
"folders;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Alt+Page down or Alt+p from the message list: allows you to go directly to "
"the attachments area without Tabbing through the text;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "<a name=\"readFromWinTab\">\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Quick Message Reading In A Separate Window Or Message Tab (F4 or Alt+Down "
"Arrow) "
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"When a message is opened in a new window, the message body is read "
"automatically by default. However, the following shortcuts allow you to hear "
"the message again at any time."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid "F4 or Alt+down arrow: quick message body reading;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid "Shift+F4 or Alt+up arrow: same function but in reverse;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "Notes:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"As a reminder, a double-press of these shortcuts starts the reading of the "
"original message;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"* Automatic reading may cause NVDA to crash on some PCs, especially if the "
"account is set to IMAP. To try resolving this issue, the Alt+d shortcut "
"opens an edit box that lets you lengthen the delay between opening the "
"window and starting automatic reading <br>\n"
"If setting this delay does not solve the problem, you may disable the "
"automatic reading via the menu Shift+[Grave](keyEquiv_en.html#aboveTab) / "
"Options for the main window / separate reading window: do not automatically "
"read message if this causes NVDA blockages;\n"
"* To make the most of uncluttered reading and protect yourself from remote "
"content that does not respect your privacy, display the body of messages in "
"simple HTML. To do this, open the View menu, scroll down to Message Body and "
"in the submenu, choose the Simple HTML option.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "Viewing columns and headers:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"It is important here to distinguish between columns and headers: the word "
"\"column\" is used below to indicate the value of a row cell in the message "
"table. The word \"header\" refers to the message itself. Headers can be "
"viewed both in the message preview pane and in the separate tab or window of "
"an open message;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "<a name=\"readCols\">\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#, no-wrap
msgid "Viewing Columns: one Digit On The Alphanumeric Keyboard "
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"These keys are for columns in the message list only. Type a number on the "
"alphanumeric keyboard without pressing the Shift key:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"A single press of a number: states the name and value of the corresponding "
"column;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid "Two presses of a number: spells the value of the corresponding column;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Three quick presses of a number: copies the column value to the "
"clipboard. To copy the addresses of the various senders and recipients, use "
"the header reading procedure discussed below;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "<a name=\"readHeaders\">\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#, no-wrap
msgid "Header Reading: Alt+one Digit On Alphanumeric Keyboard "
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"The following shortcuts can be used from the main window if the preview "
"panel is displayed (via F8) and from the separate tab or window of an open "
"message. One tap speaks the header and two taps displays a context menu as "
"appropriate;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Alt+1: one press announces the sender's name and his email address, two "
"presses open an edit box of these values. You can edit them and then press "
"Enter to copy them to the clipboard. Three presses: opens the context menu "
"of the header;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid "Alt+2: Subject with name of mailing list if any;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid "Alt+3: Message date;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Alt+4 to: main message recipients. If several recipients, three presses set "
"focus on the first recipient, then tab moves to the next one. Applications "
"key on each recipient displays the context menu;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid "Alt+5: Copy recipients;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid "Alt+6: Blind copy recipients;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid "Alt+7: \"reply to\" address;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Alt+8: User agent, if full headers are enabled via the View / headers / full "
"menu;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Alt+9: 1 press announces the number of attachments, 2 presses opens the "
"attachment list;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid "Alt+0: List of priority tags placed on a message;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Alt+[Minus](keyEquiv_en.html#bs2) or Alt+End: Gives a shortened version of "
"the status bar: number of unread messages, total number of messages and "
"quick filter expression;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid "Alt+[Equals](keyEquiv_en.html#bs1): Opens the tabs context menu;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Control+[Equals](keyEquiv_en.html#bs1): Displays the list of open tabs in a "
"menu that lets you select the chosen tab;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "<a name=\"tags\">\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#, no-wrap
msgid "Adding And Removing Priority Tags: Shift+ digit On The Alphanumeric Keyboard "
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"This feature allows you to mark a message as important or to do, for "
"instance. Next, the quick filter bar will display only messages with one or "
"more tags. For example, only important messages in the message list are "
"shown;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"To verify which tags are already placed on a message, press Alt+0 on the "
"alphanumeric keyboard."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "To add or remove a tag, press Shift+ number 1 to 9;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "<a name=\"qfb\">\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#, no-wrap
msgid "Quick Filter Bar (Letter F Or Control+Shift+K) "
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"letter F or Control+Shift+K: Displays the message quick filter bar in the "
"current folder."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Keyword filtering: Enter a keyword and press Tab to scroll through the "
"filtered list using the arrow keys;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"The down arrow key from the keyword edit box gives you access to the "
"following options list:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '    * '
msgid "1: Keep filters when changing folders? c"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '    * '
msgid "2: Show only unread messages u"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '    * '
msgid "3: Show only tracked messages s"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '    * '
msgid "4: Show only messages from persons listed in my address book d"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '    * '
msgid "5: Show only messages with tags t"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '    * '
msgid "6 : Show only messages with attachments a"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '    * '
msgid "etc."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid "Press Enter to enable or disable one or several of the mentioned criteria;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Alt+End or Alt+[Equals](keyEquiv_en.html#bs1): Allows you to hear a summary "
"of active filters and the number of filtered messages. These two shortcuts "
"also work within the message list, not just within the quick filter bar;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"When a quick filter is active, a WAV audio file is played when the list or "
"tab to which it belongs is focused. The sound resembles a breath;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"* The file filter.wav is located in the folder:\n"
"\"%appdata%\\\\NVDA\\\\TB+sounds\"\n"
"You can place a sound to your liking as long as your file is called: "
"filter.wav. After this file change, NVDA must be restarted; \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "<a name=\"tagFilter\">\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ####
#, no-wrap
msgid "Filtering By Tag "
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "When the focus is placed on the edit field of the Quick Filter bar:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '*  '
msgid ""
"Press Down Arrow until you hear \"tags\" and press Enter to check this "
"option;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '*  '
msgid ""
"Press the Tab key at that point to move to the drop-down list of tag "
"filtering modes. For example, if you choose \"to do\", only messages tagged "
"\"to do\" will be listed in the message table;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "<a name=\"colLayout\">\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#, no-wrap
msgid "Column Layout (Alt+c) "
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"The shortcut Alt+c displays a dialog that lets you change the order of the "
"columns in the message list, but also add or remove columns."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "To use it, first go to the message list or folder tree view and press Alt+c;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"The column layout dialog appears. It consists of the list of columns as well "
"as the \"Help\", \"Columns\" and \"Close\" buttons."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The \"columns...\" button     displays Thunderbird's native \"Choose Columns "
"to Display\" menu  \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"When you are in the column list, the following keyboard shortcuts are "
"available:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Left arrow: Displays the checkbox menu called \"Choose columns to "
"display\". This shortcut corresponds to the \"Columns...\" button;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Space: To move the selected column, press Space, go to another column and "
"press Space again to place the column there. This is similar to a cut and "
"paste operation;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
