#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<br>\n"
"Deactivations for Chichi and Thunderbird+:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"The main purpose of these options is to allow a good cohabitation between "
"Thunderbird+ and Chichi by avoiding duplicate features. But you can use them "
"without Chichi to suit your preferences;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "The term \"folders\" below refers to the folder tree view;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Folders: Space does not select the next unread message in the list and does "
"not display the list of unread folders d: Chichi does not yet have an "
"autonomous equivalent feature;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Folders: no navigation by initials d: by activating this option, Chichi will "
"be used. This only works from top to bottom and does not announce the "
"account name to which the activated folder belongs;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"List messages: Space does not read the message in the preview pane l: if you "
"check this option, it is Chichi that will speak the message in the preview "
"pane. Unlike Thunderbird+, this reading will not be uncluttered. On the "
"other hand, F4 and Alt+down arrow will continue to use Thunderbird+ "
"uncluttered reading;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"List messages: no SmartReply: disables the reply feature to a mailing list "
"via Control+r on single press or to the sender via Control+r on double "
"press;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"List messages: Do not handle the quick filter bar: Removes access to "
"filtering options via down arrow;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Main window: Tab does not move to the next pane: this option concerns "
"navigation between the folder tree view, the message list and the message "
"pane of headers;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Main window: Reset the escape key to its default state. This particularly "
"concerns the navigation between the panes mentioned above;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Allow Thunderbird to be closed with Control+w or Control+F4: by checking "
"this option, the forementioned two shortcuts close Thunderbird when only one "
"tab is open. This behavior is embarrassing for some people;"
msgstr ""

